# DOCS INTRODUCTIONS:  
This lab was conducted using Kali Linux running inside a virtual machine configured with VMware.  
Unlike typical Kali-based projects that focus on offensive security, this lab is strictly defensive. The objective is to apply fundamental Linux hardening techniques to a system that includes multiple preinstalled tools and active services.  
The project demonstrates how to reduce a system’s attack surface by:  
Securing user accounts  
Restricting privileges  
Controlling active services  
Limiting network exposure  
Verifying logging mechanisms  

By applying these measures, the lab reflects defensive security practices that are directly transferable to:  
Linux servers  
Enterprise infrastructures  
Cloud-based virtual machines  
Production environments  

This project reinforces the importance of proactive security configuration rather than reactive incident response.  
